	$222270: 'AA Site destroyed. Three down, two to go.',
	$222280: "There's just one left. Let's do it.",
	$222281: 'Good work airborne. I hereby declare this dropzone OPEN.',
	$222290: 'All Anti-Aircraft Guns destroyed! Good work airborne - all dropzones OPEN.',
	$222300:
		"All right - that's the last of the flak. Dropzones secure.  Primary objective complete.",
	$222310: 'Munitions point secure.  This is the firepower we needed.',
	$222312: 'Ambush... Stop and return fire!',
	$222320: 'Enemy movement, MGs react!',
	$222330:
		"Sector captured.  Until we connect it to the rest of our territory, it's no good to us.",
	$222331: 'Get off the road!',
	$222350: 'Sector connected and in supply. Good work.',
	$222410:
		'The Germans have Anti-Aircraft sites at these locations. We need to shut them down in order to open up these drop zones.',
	$222411: 'In addition, capture these strategic points to secure additional resources.',
	$222412:
		"Until a sector is clear of anti-aircraft guns, we won't be able to drop our troops there, and the drop zone will remain closed.",
	$222420: 'This road leads straight to our beachhead at Omaha.',
	$222421: "To do this, we'll need to capture these strategic points.",
	$222422: 'The landings will not succeed unless WE control this road.',
	$222423: 'Aerial recon shows that the Germans have a weapons depot here.',
	$222424: 'We might be able to raid it for some more firepower',
	$222430:
		"Germans patrols have been spotted along this road. We'll need some heavy weapons to take them out.",
	$222500: 'Some of our supply gliders crash landed north of our position',
	$222510: 'If we can get to them, we can collect heavy weapons',
	$222520: 'This is what I like to see. Bazookas and Heavy MGs. Take what you can, men.',
	$222530: 'Excellent. Mortars and MGs. Load up, squads.',
