	$240010: 'I’m going to assume that’s grape juice, sergeant.',
	$240020: 'Absolutely, sir.  Grape juice.',
	$240030: 'Well, it was grape juice...',
	$240040: '...about a year ago.',
	$240041: 'Want some?  Haaah.  Wait your turn. Hey hey!',
	$240050: '<laughter>',
	$240051: 'Mmmm, 1943! That was a nice year.',
	$240060: 'Listen up ladies, R&R is over.',
	$240070: 'The 17th SS Panzer Division is mobilizing to retake Carentan.',
	$240080: 'We just have one job to do here: HOLD THE TOWN.',
	$240090: 'They need the bridges. We have to defend them.',
	$240100:
		'MG Emplacements, mines and wire obstacles at these points will hold off the krauts... for a while.',
	$240101:
		'MG Emplacements, mines and wire obstacles at these points will hold off the Germans... for a while.',
	$240110: 'We have a couple of 57mm A-T guns to cover the approaches into the town.',
	$240120: 'We’ll need to keep them safe.',
	$240130:
		'Engineers have established a FIELD BARRACKS at the Town Hall and the Church. We can call in reinforcements from these locations at any time.',
	$240140: 'Strategic Points have been spotted across the river at these positions.  Capture them.',
	$240150: 'The Jerries will want Carentan back, so let’s dig in and make ‘em pay for it.',
	$240160: "Let's go ladies!",
	$240170: 'Show these bastards what Airborne troops are made of!',
	$240240: 'Goddamn!',
	$240250: 'Fall back!',
	$240260: 'The town square’s overrun.',
	$240270: 'Goddamn!',
	$240280: 'Fall back!',
	$240290: 'The town square’s overrun.',
	$240300: 'Withdraw to the church and defend it at all costs.',
	$240320: 'Stugs!',
	$240330: 'Stugs! They have Stugs!',
	$240340: 'Panzers!',
	$240350: 'Where’s our support?',
	$240360: 'Use Recoilless Rifles and hit their side or rear armor',
	$240370: 'Get those Recoilless Rifles and flank those tanks',
	$240380: "We're too close! Use satchel charges!",
	$240390: 'Get close to that stug and blow it!',
	$240400: 'We got axis movement on the bridges!',
	$240410: 'The krauts have breached the lines, they’re crossing the river.',
	$240420: 'German penetration along the west bridge.',
	$240430: 'German penetration along the central bridge.',
	$240440: 'German penetration along the east bridge',
	$240450: 'We’re losing our strategic points.',
	$240460: 'Make sure the Krauts DO NOT cross the bridges!',
	$240470: 'Hold the line!',
	$240480: 'Keep those tanks away from the church!',
	$240490: "Push 'em back!",
	$240500: "They're closing on the church!",
	$240510: 'Church surrounded!',
	$240520: 'The church is surrounded!',
	$240530: 'The church is under fire!',
	$240531: 'Attention Fox Company, this is Able Company entering Carentan from the West.',
	$240532: "We've brought some Armor from the beaches.",
	$240534: "Roger that Able, it's good to have you.",
	$240536: 'We could sure use your help',
	$240540: 'God damn! Good to see some of our tanks for a change!',
	$240550: 'Now move up and push the Germans out of Carentan!',
	$240560: 'Hey! Looks like Able Company has finally arrived!',
	$240570: 'It’s about time fellas!  We started to think maybe you boys got lost!',
	$240580: 'Yeah, well we got a little hung up on the beach.',
	$240600:
		'Looks like the last of Able Company is all here.  Baker and Dog Companies are about an hour out.',
	$240610: 'We should have forces from both beaches joined up by nightfall.',
	$240620: 'We’re going to need all the supplies from the depot station... <inaudible>',
	$240670: 'The US First Army is marching north up the Cotenin peninsula,',
	$240680: 'so securing the supply line to Cherbourg is our new objective.',
	$240690: 'It has been code-named the RED BALL EXPRESS.',
	$240700: 'Able and Dog companies will penetrate down this road as far as possible and secure it.',
	$240710: 'During the advance, our flanks will be exposed.',
	$240720: 'This area has a lot of walled courtyards & hedgerows, so watch for ambush.',
	$240800: "It's too damn quiet out here, watch for snipers.",
	$240810: 'Sniper! Take Cover.',
	$240860: 'Engineers!  Lay some mines and barbed wire on those bridges!',
	$240870: 'Cover the approaches to the bridges with MG emplacements and anti-tank guns',
	$240880: 'Get some recoilless rifles and garrison those buildings',
	$240890: 'We have to hold hold them off.',
