	$290001: 'What’s the matter Franks?',
	$290002: 'Never seen a dead body before?',
	$290030:
		"For three days our division has been trying to capture Hill 192. The German 352nd Grenadier holds it, we're gonna take it.",
	$290050:
		"We'll be clawing our way uphill, against entrenched positions hidden in the hedgerows so watch your flanks.",
	$290080:
		"That's not all, the 352nd is reinforcing from these towns. If we can secure these areas, it'll stop them from attacking our line of advance.",
	$290090: 'Listen up, Able Company.  We need a way to cut through these hedgerows.',
	$290100: 'Deploy Sherman Crocodiles and upgrade them with bulldozer blades.',
	$290120: 'Panzer!',
	$290130: "Jerry's got armor here!",
	$290140: 'Artillery!  Incoming!',
	$290150: 'The Germans are using a tower and are spotting our positions.  Take it out.',
	$290160: "They got 88's covering the road!",
	$290161: 'Taking fire! They got an 88!',
	$290170: 'Stay off the road and find some way to flank it.',
	$290190: 'Goliath Incoming!',
	$290200: "They're hitting us with Goliaths here!",
	$290210: 'Goliath! Watch out!',
	$290220: 'The Germans are reinforcing their left flank from here.',
	$290230: 'I want to see that town in ruins, now!',
	$290240: "We can't have Jerry coming in and cutting off our advance.",
	$290250: 'This is where Charlie Company got ambushed.',
	$290260: 'We should secure this town to protect our right flank.',
	$290280: 'The Germans are using the hedgerows to flank our main line of advance.',
	$290290: 'Defend our flanks by deploying MGs and mortar squads along the hedgerows.',
	$290310: 'Now that we have Hill 192 we are in position to take Saint Lo.',
	$290311:
		'Recon indicates the town is already in very bad shape and the Germans are going to be dug in deep.',
	$290312: '...there will be a lot of cover and obstacles in this terrain...',
	$290330: "Without those dozers on our Shermans we're not going anywhere.",
	$290340: 'Crush the hedgerows to avoid chokepoints',
	$293001:
		"The hedgerows are heavily defended. This means we'll be clawing our way uphill, under intense fire so watch your flanks.",
	$293002: 'Expect these two roads to be well defended, avoid them for as long as you can.',
	$293003:
		"Taking Hill 192 won't be easy.  Charlie Company was wiped out trying to take this hill.  Now it's up to us.",
	$293004: 'Good luck Able.',
	$293005: 'Taking automatic fire from the hedgerows!',
	$293006: 'Down and fast, taking fire from the hedgerows',
