	$349670: 'Start',
	$349671: '1st Axis Base Destroyed',
	$349672: '2nd Axis Base Destroyed',
	$349673: 'Axis Under 300 Points',
	$349674: 'Axis Under 200 Points',
	$349675: 'Axis Under 100 Points',
	$350002: 'Columns of vehicles from the 2nd Panzer Division are escaping through this town.',
	$350010:
		"Baker Company's last report was that they were engaging Shultz' Tigergruppen. This means the Tiger Ace is defending the town.",
	$350011: 'We need to take him out.',
	$350020: "It won't be easy to get a kill shot - he most likely has Heavy Panzer support.",
	$350030: 'Now if we can take down Shultz, the krauts will be finished here.',
	$350050: 'Tiger! Take cover!',
	$350070: 'We gotta flank him!',
	$350150: 'Our Allied air support is useless with those flak panzers around',
	$350160: 'We need to take them out',
	$350181: 'Alright, second squad, take the left flank.  Keep your eyes open.',
	$350182: 'First squad, on me.',
	$350183: "Hey guys, wasn't this Schultz the one who killed the Captain?",
	$350184: "Yeah, didn't he almost kill you too, Lieutenant?",
	$350185: 'Shut the fuck up, Cunningham.',
	$350186: 'Shutting up, sir.',
	$350187: "Alright, there's nothing to see here.  We're moving out.",
	$350189: 'That guy was one tough kraut.',
	$350190: 'The 300,000 strong German Seventh Army is in full retreat.',
	$350191:
		'Our objective is to cut them off and prevent them from crossing the Rhine and setting up a defensive line',
	$350192: 'British, Canadian and Polish forces are moving in from the north.',
	$350193: 'US Divisions led by Able company, will seal the pocket from the south.',
	$350194: 'Having achieved air superiority, we can strike the retreating German convoys at will.',
	$350195:
		'All of what we have achieved since D-Day now hangs in the balance. If we prevail, the fate of the German army will be sealed and the war for Europe will be won.',
	$353006: "Alright get that Pershing tank up front and center.  It's got a job to do.",
	$353008: 'Tiiiiger!',
	$353009: 'Use our air support!',
	$353010: 'Tiger!  Call in an air strike!',
