	$407583: 'The Panzerschreck is an excellent Anti Tank weapon, but slow to fire.',
	$407584:
		'They also provide basic logistical support through building base structures and repairing damaged vehicles.',
	$407585: 'Good. Your Panzer Grenadiers have left the halftrack.',
	$407600: 'Recon reports an enemy infantry squad occupying a nearby Slit Trench.',
	$407601: 'Recon reports an enemy infantry squad occupying a nearby Building.',
	$407602: 'Recon reports an entrenched infantry squad up ahead.',
	$407603: "Let's take them out.",
	$407604:
		'This is a MORTAR HALFTRACK. This mobile artillery vehicle is quite effective at dealing with entrenched infantry.',
	$407605: 'Order the Mortar Halftrack to fire an incendiary barrage at the enemy infantry squad.',
	$407606: 'Left-Click on the flashing INCENDIARY MORTAR button.',
	$407607: 'Good, now Left-Click on the enemy squad to target it.',
	$407608: 'Excellent! Bombardment underway.',
	$407609:
		'Good. However, you missed the enemy. Try it again, but target the infantry squad this time.',
	$407610:
		"You'll notice your barrage was only marginally effective. Several more barrages are needed to fully defeat the enemy squad.",
	$407611:
		'Look at the Incendiary Barrage button, the ability has a long recharge time, preventing you from issuing additional barrages.',
	$407612: "Let's call in resupply support, the MUNITIONS HALFTRACK.",
	$407613:
		'This vehicle resupplies nearby units by greatly reducing the recharge time of their abilities.',
	$407614: 'Order the Munitions Halftrack to move closer to your Mortar Halftrack.',
	$407615: 'The Munitions Halftrack is not close enough to the Mortar Halftrack. Move it closer.',
	$407616:
		'Good. The Munitions Halftrack is within resupply range. This is indicated by the symbol above the Mortar Halftrack.',
	$407617:
		'Notice the Incendiary Mortar ability recharges faster if the Munitions Halftrack is nearby.',
	$407618: 'Notice the Incendiary Mortar ability. It is fully charged and ready to fire.',
	$407619: 'Order the halftrack to barrage the infantry with incendiary rounds again.',
	$407620: 'Notice that the ability recharges almost instantly now.',
	$407621: 'Continue to barrage the enemy squad until they are defeated.',
	$407622: 'Excellent job, infantry neutralized!',
	$407623:
		'Since your Mortar Halftrack is mobile, you will want the Munitions Halftrack to MAINTAIN SUPPORT RANGE.',
	$407624: 'Order the Munitions Halftrack to follow the Mortar Halftrack.',
	$407625:
		'Left-Click on the flashing button then LEFT-CLICK on the Mortar Halftrack to follow it.',
	$407626:
		'You did not target the Mortar Halftrack! Re-select the Munitions Halftrack and try again.',
	$407627:
		'Good. An ICON has appeared above the Munitions Halftrack to indicate that it is following the Mortar Halftrack.',
	$407628: 'Enemy Patrol spotted!',
	$407629: 'Use your INCENDIARY BARRAGE to take them out.',
	$407630:
		'Because your Munitions Halftrack is linked to the Mortar Halftrack, it follows it closely to continue resupplying.',
	$407631: 'Excellent, enemy partrol is down.',
	$407632:
		'At some point you may want to break the link between your Mortar and Munitions Halftracks.',
	$407633:
		'This is done by simply ordering your Munitions Halftrack to move without selecting the Mortar Halftrack.',
	$407634: 'Good job, your Munitions Halftrack has stopped following the other Halftrack.',
	$407635: 'Good. The Munitions Halftrack is within resupply range.',
	$407650: "For our next objective, let's capture and secure a territory.",
	$407651: 'This is the SCOUT CAR, a Panzer Elite vehicle that can CAPTURE Strategic Points.',
	$407653: 'Order the Scout Car to CAPTURE the indicated STRATEGIC POINT by RIGHT-CLICKING it.',
	$407654: 'You have stopped capturing the Strategic Point.',
	$407655:
		'The Scout Car is an excellent recon vehicle. Armed with an MG42 light machine gun, it is excellent for defeating lightly equipped infantry squads.',
	$407656: 'Good job, the sector is now in our control. Now time to secure it.',
	$407658: "To secure this sector, you'll need to upgrade your Scout Car first.",
	$407659: 'LEFT-CLICK on the flashing button to equip this vehicle with LOGISTIK SUPPORT.',
	$407660: 'With this Logistik Support upgrade, the Scout Car is able to secure territory.',
	$407661:
		'Good. The radio antenna now attached to the roof of your Scout Car indicates that it has been upgraded to a LOGISTIK CAR.',
	$407662:
		'Your Scout Car has is not in the captured territory. Order the Scout Car to move to the indicated position.',
	$407663: 'LEFT-CLICK on the flashing button to SECURE this SECTOR.',
	$407664: 'Good job, the territory is now secure.',
	$407665: 'Notice that a Scout Car securing territory is immobile.',
	$407666:
		'To mobilize the Scout Car, Left-Click on the Secure Sector button again. However, the territory will no longer be secured.',
	$407667:
		'Now that the territory is captured and secure. We need to bring in some heavier weapons to protect the Scout Car.',
	$407668:
		'This is a Panzer IV F Infantry Support Tank, affectionately referred to as the "Stubby", for its short cannon.',
	$407669: 'Order the Panzer to move to the indicated position within the captured territory.',
	$407670: 'Achtung! Incoming enemy.',
	$407671: "Notice the Panzer's slow rate of fire.",
	$407672: 'You can increase its rate of fire by using its RAPID FIRE ability.',
	$407673: 'LEFT-CLICK on the flashing RAPID FIRE button to lock the Panzer down.',
	$407674:
		'Good job, the Panzer is able to fire more quickly, however, it is now locked down and cannot move.',
	$407675: 'Another squad is attacking our position.',
	$407677:
		'Many vehicles in the Panzer Elite have the ability to Lock Down. However, the benefits differ from vehicle to vehicle.',
	$407678:
		'As a Panzer Elite commander, knowing when to sacrfice mobilty for firepower is crucial for victory.',
	$407679: 'To re-mobilize the Panzer. Left-Click on the Rapid Fire button again.',
	$407680: 'Good job, you can now move your Panzer.',
	$407681: 'Notice your Panzer was promoted to VETERAN status.',
	$407682:
		'When Panzer Elite squads and vehicles gain Veterancy, this unlocks two special skills allowing you to customize the combat effectiveness of the unit.',
	$407683: 'In the Command Panel, there are two VETERANCY buttons.',
	$407684: "The first ability boosts the unit's OFFENSIVE power, the second, its DEFENSIVE power.",
	$407685: 'With each rank of Veterancy, you can choose which ability to apply to the unit.',
	$407686: 'Left-Click on one of the flashing buttons to apply the bonus.',
	$407687: 'Good. Your Panzer has been granted an Offensive Veterancy bonus.',
	$407688: 'Intel reports approaching tanks!',
	$407689:
		"The Panzer IV F's gun is no match for the heavy British Armor. Time to call in the Luftwaffe Company Commander.",
	$407690:
		'You have been granted access to the HENSCHEL STRAFING RUN. It is a very effective Anti Tank air strike.',
	$407692: 'Left-Click on the flashing HENSCHEL STRAFING ability button.',
	$407693: 'Now, Left-Click to target the indicated position for Air Strikes.',
	$407694: 'Now, Left-Click to target the indicated Tank for Air Strikes.',
	$407695:
		'With this ability, Henschel Aircraft will fly-by the target location, targeting all enemies within their flight path.',
	$407696:
		'The Panzer Elite have two other Company Commanders besides the Luftwaffe. These specialize in Scorched Earth and Tank Destroyer Tactics.',
	$407697: 'Tank threat eliminated!',
	$407698:
		'Now you know about some of the unique aspects to the Panzer Elite. You learned about the three types of Halftracks, infantry and vehicle combat, vehicle capturing and securing, and finally, veterancy and lock down.',
	$407699: 'Excellent work. Panzer Elite training complete. Dismissed.',
