	$551000: 'New Player Information',
	$551001:
		"Welcome to the Company of Heroes news page! Here you'll find the latest updates on everything related to Company of Heroes, such as the release of new maps, balance tweaks, and patches. You'll also find exciting announcements for other great Relic titles. Remember, if you don't see it here - it isn't official Company of Heroes news!",
	$551002: 'New Player Information',
	$551003:
		'The Chat tab is the hub of your Company of Heroes experience. Using an IRC-style interface, you can see who is in a channel at any particular time. The best thing about Chat? You can use it at any time, even while waiting for a Ranked Match to begin. No need to worry about losing your Ranked Match session - just set your parameters, then come in here and Chat away until the game starts.',
	$551004: 'New Player Information',
	$551005:
		"Setting up a multiplayer game couldn't be easier, thanks to the Game Setup tab. Here you can choose the map, set victory conditions, leave open slots available for other players to join - even check their spec rating to ensure that the game won't slow down due to a bad connection. With a chat window available, you can talk smack until the game starts.",
	$551006: 'New Player Information',
	$551007:
		'Listings of games are displayed here. Each game shows the map name, number of players already connected to that game, the maximum number of players for that map, and the average ping of the players connected to that game.',
	$551008: 'New Player Information',
	$551009:
		'The Statistics screen contains the leaderboards for every permutation you can think of. 1v1 all the way to 4v4, Axis vs Allies, Everyone vs Friends.',
	$551010: 'New Player Information',
	$551011: 'The Options screen allows you to turn on and off information boxes.',
	$551012: 'New Player Information',
	$551013:
		'When creating a game, you can elect to leave it open or use password protection so only approved players can enter your private session.',
	$551014: 'New Player Information',
	$551015:
		"Automatches create games that match players of similar skill, and these games affect online rankings. You can see how many players are looking for a Ranked Match, and can let the system know Preferred Maps, Match Type, and Army preferences. After clicking on Start to accept, you can use the other tabs at the top of the screen and when a Ranked Match is found, you'll automatically enter the gameplay session.",
	$551016: 'New Player Information',
	$551017:
		'The Game History screen is where you can manage all the information gathered about games you have played. This includes saved games from both the campaigns and skirmishes, as well as any replays you have saved or downloaded.',
	$551018: 'New Player Information',
	$551019:
		"The Rewards screen displays all the medals, awards and unlockable units you have earned. You can swap out unlockable units for existing units to change your Army's strategy within Classic multiplayer matches.",
	$551020: '...',
	$551021: 'Instructions',
	$551022:
		'Stonewall Objective:\\n- You and your team must defend your HQ against successive waves of enemies of increasing difficulty.\\n\\nResources: \\n- Players will obtain resources by defeating the invading enemy units, with more powerful units providing a higher resource value. \\n- From time to time, players will receive a free ability for surviving various waves, these abilities only have one use so use them wisely! \\n\\nSpawning Buildings: \\n- The structure in the middle of the map can be used to build and upgrade units. \\n- Outpost buildings along the perimeter can provide limited production support, and possess limited reinforcement capabilities. \\n- Outpost buildings can provide healing for your units, +10 extra population cap, or a continual manpower bonus. \\n- If there is more than one player the outpost buildings will be owned by nobody – the players must decide amongst themselves who will capture each building. \\n\\nOpposition: \\n- As the waves wear on, stronger and deadlier enemies will appear. \\n- As the difficulty increases the invaders will come in greater numbers and in multiple directions as well. \\n- As each new wave type appears, a warning message and indicator will also appear, informing the player of where the next attack will come from.',
	$551023: 'Instructions',
	$551024:
		"Panzerkrieg Objective: \\n- Go head to head against your foes in Panzerkrieg controlling a single tank. Kill your enemies in order to lower their victory point score. The more formidable your foe, the more Victory Points he will lose for his team after his tank is destroyed. \\n\\nPick your Tank Ace:\\n- Each tank contains different abilities and upgrades, so choose the Tank Ace that best suits your play style. Dominate the field, massacre lowly infantry and watch as your friends flee in terror.\\n\\nControl the Battlefield: \\n- Capture victory points and hold them to slowly chip away at your victory point score. It may not be the most glorious route to victory, but losing isn't so glorious either. \\n- In addition to bringing your victory point counter down, each victory point under your control grants access to helpful abilities for controlling the map.\\n\\n- Control the Mortar Bunker to drop artillery on the battlefield. \\n -Capture the Radio Tower for Off-Map Support.\\n- Command the Infantry Victory Point to gain access to a more diverse set of Infantry Reinforcements.",
	$551025: 'Instructions',
	$551026:
		'Assault Objective:\\n- Push against your opponents defenses and help your Soldiers win victories to reach the enemy HQ.\\n- Destroy the enemy HQ complex.\\n\\nUnits:\\n- Play as a Hero and choose from a Commando, Heavy Weapons Specialist, Medic, Recon, Engineer/Pioneer, Officer, and Sniper.\\n- Each unit contains its own unique collection of active and passive abilities.\\n\\nLevel Progression:\\n- Players may level up their Heroes by defeating enemy soldiers and vehicles.\\n- As Heroes gain levels the player will be granted resource to improve their Hero.\\n- Players may change their Hero choice upon death, retaining all levels and upgrades earned.',
	$551027: 'Instructions',
	$551028:
		'Domination Objective:\\n- Capture and hold islands until the enemy Victory Point ticker reaches zero.\\n\\n Units: \\n- Squads are built from the "Forward Barracks" in the central area of the island.\\n- Any island that is fully captured by a team will enable the “Forward Barracks” for that team.\\n\\n Territory:\\n- Capture all of the territory in the island to own that island.\\n- If an enemy player destroys the “Forward Barracks” on an island that island will become neutrally owned.\\n\\n Resources:\\n- Players slowly accrue resources over time but also get a big boost every few minutes depending on how many islands are owned by the team.\\n- When the timer reaches zero a box of resources will paradrop down on a random island.\\n\\n Commander Abilities:\\n- Capturing more islands will unlock more Commander Abilities for use.\\n- Losing islands required for a Commander Ability will result in a loss of the ability as well.',
