	$704520: 'Text placed in this area must meet a minimum standard of excellence.',
	$704521: '2p_Senois (map name)',
	$704522: 'Press any key to start the game',
	$704523:
		'Use protection offered by walls and hedges for cover while you move around the battlefield.',
	$704524:
		'Units in cover take less damage, less suppression, and recover suppression faster than units in the open.',
	$704525:
		'Buildings offer great protection for your troops. Some armies can occupy these buildings to deploy more units.',
	$704526:
		'Flamethrowers, grenades, tank fire, and artillery are useful for clearing enemies out of buildings.',
	$704527:
		'Tanks are vulnerable from the side and from behind. Remember to keep your vehicle’s front armor pointed towards your enemy.',
	$704528:
		'Short range weapons, like Submachine Guns and Assault Rifles, are best used aggressively.',
	$704529:
		'Flanking enemy squads is an effective tactic; you can negate cover by firing from the side.',
	$704530:
		'Move your units around behind buildings or tall walls. Your units will be well protected from fire.',
	$704531:
		'Attacking with a longer range unit, or using suppression for instance, and then closing with a short range unit is a good tactic.',
	$704532:
		'It is cheaper to reinforce your squad than build a new one. Retreat your units to your headquarters to avoid taking unnecessary losses.',
	$704533:
		'Holding SHIFT+Right-Clicking will queue up commands for your units. Your units will follow your orders in the sequence you choose.',
	$704534:
		'Squads are more vulnerable to enemy fire while building, repairing or capturing territory.',
	$704535:
		'When units are in heavy cover, direct assaults are not advised. However, you can use grenades and flamethrowers to counter the benefits of cover.',
	$704536:
		'Suppression fire can slow units down, forcing them to remain in your area of fire for longer.',
	$704537:
		'A minefield can protect an open flank; enemy units will attempt to flank your weapon or squad, and run into a well placed mine.',
	$704538:
		'Many long range weapons can actually shoot beyond their own sight radius. Use forward infantry or stealthy units to sight for HMGs, mortars, and AT guns.',
	$704539:
		'An HMG with a rifle squad for defense is a good combination. The Infantry units can prevent enemy units from flanking the machine gun.',
	$704540:
		'Mortars and machine guns work well together - the HMG can suppress, and the mortar can drop shells on the suppressed infantry.',
	$704541:
		'Keep a couple of squads of infantry, or some light tanks and armoured cars to defend rear areas against the enemy.',
	$704542:
		'Early in the game, very few units can break through the heavy defenses or cover (tank traps, hedgerows). Keep your support weapons covering these natural chokepoints.',
	$704543:
		'All tanks have weaker rear and side armor. Instead of setting up AT guns to face the attack head on, set them to the flanks of the attack.',
	$704544:
		'Infantry in buildings, bunkers, artillery, machine guns, are easy targets for tanks or the heavy armored cars.',
	$704545: 'Use smoke intelligently. Smoke can screen units from fire, offering excellent cover.',
	$704546:
		'Reduce enemy resource income and population cap by disconnecting territory at key points.',
	$704547: 'Units that are moving are less accurate when firing than when stationary.',
	$704548:
		'A sniper’s firing range is greater than his line-of-sight. Use a bike or jeep to spot for your sniper.',
	$704549:
		'Some resource points are higher than others. Controlling the highest resource points can be a deciding factor in a game.',
	$704550: 'You can hear enemy vehicles and infantry approach even through the Fog of War.',
	$704551: 'Units garrisoned in buildings and vehicles cannot be suppressed or pinned.',
	$704552: 'Capturing strategic points increases your maximum population cap.',
	$704553:
		'Vehicles travel faster on roads and will often choose roads to get to their destination. This makes roads an ideal spot to lay mines.',
	$704554:
		'Some units need to be set up to face the right direction, such as machine gun nests and anti-tank crews. Hold the right mouse button down and drag in the direction you want them to face.',
	$704555:
		'Right-clicking on a name in the lobby allows you to add him or her as a friend. Being friends with a player makes it easy for you to invite the player to a game or chat.',
	$704556:
		'Off-map artillery deals massive damage but tends to cost a lot of munitions; use it wisely to maximize the number of casualties inflicted.',
	$704557:
		'Use mines to act as a soft anti-vehicle measure to stop advancing vehicles from entering your territory.',
	$704558:
		'Most roads offer negative cover and are very dangerous for infantry. Be sure to cross them quickly to prevent casualties.',
	$704559:
		'Halftracks have the ability to reinforce nearby squads. Use this tactic offensively to reinforce on the battlefield.',
	$704560:
		'If your view is obstructed, try rotating your camera by holding down the ALT key and moving the mouse. Hit the BACKSPACE key twice to return your camera to the default view.',
	$704561:
		'Operations are new multiplayer modes for Tales of Valor.  Operations let you experience Company of Heroes in a variety of exciting modes, from heroic last stands to major tank battles.',
	$704562:
		'In Tales of Valor, play Operation Panzerkrieg! Up to six players battle head-to-head in this epic showdown of tank commanders.',
	$704563:
		'Operation Panzerkrieg: Heavy tanks are worth more Victory Points when they are destroyed than light tanks.',
	$704564:
		'Operation Panzerkrieg: There are two paths to victory -- destroying enemy tanks or controlling Victory Points.',
	$704565:
		'Operation Panzerkrieg: Not all tanks capture Victory Points at the same speed. Light tanks capture points faster than heavy tanks.',
	$704566:
		'Operation Panzerkrieg: If your tank is heavily damaged, move it back to a nearby Repair Station to quickly repair the tank and return to battle.',
	$704567:
		"In Tales of Valor, play Operation Assault! Players battle to topple the enemy's defensive lines while dismantling their emplacements, until finally striking a deadly blow against the enemy HQ.",
	$704568:
		'To enable the reward vehicles for Tales of Valor in a multiplayer game, simply click the checkbox in the Vehicles tab found on the Rewards page in the lobby.',
	$704569:
		"Operation Assault: Taking out your enemy's HMG emplacements will allow you to shift the front lines of the battle.",
	$704570:
		"Operation Assault: Don't get so attached! Certain heroes in Operation Assault make great early-game progress, while some flourish later on. Change heroes after you have died!",
	$704571:
		"Operation Assault: Destroying the MG nests near to a mortar bunker will neutralize it.  Neutralized mortar bunkers can't fire at you or recruit enemy soldiers!",
	$704572:
		'Operation Assault: If you are too hurt to continue the fight, return to a friendly Mortar Bunker to quickly heal your hero and continue the battle.',
	$704573:
		'In Tales of Valor, play Operation Stonewall! Stand guard with your friends and protect your HQ as the enemy hurls wave after wave of increasingly powerful counterattacks.',
	$704574:
		'Operation Stonewall: Protect your HQ at all costs! Without it, you will lose the ability to purchase upgrades and unlock new units.',
	$704575:
		'Operation Stonewall: If playing with multiple allies, try specializing in either infantry or vehicles to better prepare yourself for the enemy assault.',
	$704576:
		'Operation Stonewall: Capturing the Church confers a healing bonus to nearby infantry for you and your allies.',
	$704577:
		'Operation Stonewall: If you capture The Manor at the beginning, it increases your individual Population Cap.',
	$704578:
		"Operation Stonewall: You and your allies' vehicles will automatically be repaired when parked near a captured Garage.",
	$704579:
		'Operation Stonewall: If you capture The Bank at the beginning, it will boost your individual manpower rate.',
	$704580:
		'Customize your army with the new reward vehicles in the Rewards tab. Exchange one of the existing vehicles with a new one from Tales of Valor.',
