	$1320500: 'Lieutenant Bailey, front and center.',
	$1320510: 'Before 3rd Battalion deploys into the area we need to secure this strategic point.',
	$1320520: "You've pulled the short stick.",
	$1320530: 'Assemble your troops and recce the area.',
	$1320540: "2nd Lieutenant's!",
	$1320550: 'Muckle onto those sections and sort them out!',
	$1320560: 'Once attached, have those sections move up LTs.',
	$1320570: 'Steady up gents.',
	$1320580: "We've got whistle heads latching onto us.",
	$1320590: 'Make sure you give it that extra effort.',
	$1320600: 'Dillingham, square your lads away, mate.',
	$1320610: 'Area has been secured.',
	$1320620: 'Ready to call in 3rd Battalion HQ Command Post.',
	$1320630: 'Get it set up right bloody quick!',
	$1320640: "Position's marked, move now!",
	$1320650: '3rd Battalion HQ reporting.',
	$1320660: 'Additional infantry, officer and Bren Carrier reinforcements available Lt. Bailey.',
	$1320670: 'Field Support is standing by, have the Mobile HQ deploy it when ready.',
	$1320680:
		"Having the vehicle deployed in an area secures that territory, so the enemy can't recapture it.",
	$1320690: 'When necessary it can be torn down and packed for movement.',
	$1320700: 'For now leave it in this area.',
	$1320710: 'Corporal Degnan!',
	$1320720: 'Sort the troops out and reorg as needed.',
	$1320730: 'I want the adjacent sector cleared out and secured.',
	$1320740: 'Any particular one?',
	$1320750: 'Use your initiative, Degnan.',
	$1320760: "You don't want to stay a Corporal the whole war, do you?",
	$1320770: 'About bloody time Bailey.',
	$1320780: 'Get over to the HQ vehicle and call up the mobile Field Support Command Post.',
	$1320790: 'Once their Infantry CP is set up call in additional sections.',
	$1320791: 'Get over to the HQ vehicle and call up the mobile Command Post.',
	$1320810: 'Get those lazy Service Battalion wankers to set up the command post.',
	$1320820: "As soon as they're in place we'll be able to call up Sappers and light armor.",
	$1320830: 'Right gents, rifles at the ready.',
	$1320840: 'Sounds like a Recce mission.',
	$1320850: 'Watch for Jerry snipers.',
	$1320860: 'Making sure the area is nice and safe are we?',
	$1320870: 'Shut your gob before they give us shite duty.',
	$1320880: 'Major Blackmore, 3rd Battalion is in position.',
	$1320890: 'Awaiting orders major...',
	$1320900: 'We need to recce the bridges.',
	$1320910: 'Use the Staurt Tanks with infantry support and scout the bridges.',
	$1320920: 'The bank is crawling with bloody Germans!',
	$1320930: "Fuckin' hell!  Look at the other side of the river!",
	$1320940: "It's a whole other fuckin' German company!",
	$1320950: "Tell those fuckin' Stuarts to use their bloody Anti-pers canisters!",
	$1320960: "Mow 'em down with the Anti-pers rounds!",
	$1320970: 'Cover and move!  Use each other for support damn it!',
	$1320980: "Get recce groups on those fuckin' bridges!",
	$1320990: 'This is what you call a target rich environment you crooked tooth bastards!',
	$1321000: 'Where the fuck are all these god damn Huns coming from!',
	$1321010: "Bloody hell mate, they're using the wooden bridges to get across!",
	$1321020: "There's more of 'em!",
	$1321030: 'Bloody hell! The bridge is wired!',
	$1321040: "It's fuckin' wired!  Get off, move!",
	$1321050: "Stay off the bridge, it's rigged to blow! Move, move!",
	$1321060: 'Löschen Sie die Brücke!',
	$1321070: 'Fünf',
	$1321080: 'Vier',
	$1321090: 'Drei',
	$1321100: 'Zwei',
	$1321110: 'Eins',
	$1321120: 'Die Briten kommen! Löschen Sie die Brücke!',
	$1321130: 'Help the wounded!  We need to find another way across!',
	$1321140: "I guess the recce's finished here!",
	$1321150: 'Fallback!  We need to make another crossing!',
	$1321160: 'Let Battalion know the bridge is blown!',
	$1321170: "I think that fuckin' massive explosion gave it away!",
	$1321180: "No fuckin' shit!",
	$1321190: 'I think Darwin was on the bridge when she blew! God rest his soul.',
	$1321200: "Take out those fuckin' MGs!!",
	$1321210: "Neil's tit's up mate!",
	$1321220: "They've got MG's covering the approaches!",
	$1321240: 'Degnan! Get the men onto the remaining bridge.',
	$1321250: "I don't care what you do but secure that remaining bridge!",
	$1321260: "Jerry's got another crossing!",
	$1321270: "They're counter-attacking from the wooden bridge!",
	$1321280: 'I want a defensive screen around our command posts!',
	$1321290: 'Get the Sappers to throw up emplacements!',
	$1321300: 'Go on, get a message to Captain Wallis, move!',
	$1321310: "Fuckin' bullshite.",
	$1321320: 'Captain Wallis, sir!',
	$1321330: 'We need Sappers to deploy emplacements!',
	$1321340: "They're yours, Corporal!",
	$1321350: 'That bridge is repairable, sir!',
	$1321360: 'Then get your arse over there!',
	$1321370: 'Where the bloody hell is Corporal Degnan?',
	$1321380: 'We need covering fire for our lads!',
	$1321390: "We've got a heavy sodding defensive line here!",
	$1321400: 'Where the hell are Royal Scots and their Heavy Tanks!?',
	$1321410: "You'd think Woods could light a fire under their arse!",
	$1321420: 'Lieutenant Bailey! Heavy Tank reporting!',
	$1321430: "You've got your Churchills!",
	$1321440: 'Armored Vehicle, Royal Engineer, A-V-R-E standing by.',
	$1321450: 'Good timing, sir!',
	$1321460: 'DEGNAN!',
	$1321470: 'Link up with those Churchills and have them neutralize that blockade!',
	$1321480: 'WE NEED TO CROSS that river at any cost.',
	$1321490: 'Contact! AT Gun!',
	$1321500: "On the fuckin' riverbank! Pak 38!",
	$1321510: "They've got the bridge covered with AT guns!",
	$1321520: "There's another Pak 38!",
	$1321530: "Incoming!  They've got us dialed in!",
	$1321540: "Sir!  We've got arty rockets zeroed in on us!",
	$1321550: 'We need to find those field rockets!',
	$1321560: 'Get sections up there!',
	$1321570: 'Those nebs need to be neutralized ASAP!',
	$1321580: "We've got Nebelwerfers on the hill!",
	$1321590:
		"There's heavy backblast from the other side of the river! It must be the Nebelwerfers!",
