	$6000000: 'Tiger Ace',
	$6000001:
		'Assault the town of Villers-Bocage and prevent the British 2nd Army from flanking the Panzer Lehr Division and reaching Caen.',
	$6000050: 'Villers-Bocage: Birth of a Legend',
	$6000052: 'VILL1',
	$6000054:
		'Tank Commander Hauptmann Maximillian Voss and Gunner Feldwebel Joseph Shultz ambush an unsuspecting British convoy from the famed Desert Rats!',
	$6000056: 'Villers-Bocage, Normandy.',
	$6000058: '0717hrs. June 13th 1944',
	$6000060: 'Retreat from Villers-Bocage',
	$6000062: 'VILL2',
	$6000064:
		'After successfully halting the British 7th Armoured Division "the Desert Rats," Voss orders his crew to abandon their disabled tank. The Tigergruppe must escape Villers-Bocage on foot and head back to Point 213.',
	$6000066: 'Villers-Bocage, Normandy.',
	$6000068: '1026hrs. June 13th 1944',
	$6000070: 'An Ace Reborn',
	$6000072: 'VILL3',
	$6000074:
		'Safely back at Division HQ, Voss and his Tigergruppe requisition a new Tiger tank and renew their attack. Supported by 901st Panzergrenadier Lehr Regiment, their orders are to secure Villers-Bocage and halt the British advance.',
	$6000076: 'Villers-Bocage, Normandy.',
	$6000078: '1602hrs. June 13th 1944',
	$6000079: 'Villers-Bocage (6)',
	$6000080:
		"A picturesque city in the peaceful rolling hills of France. Deserted by it's former inhabitants, the once busy streets have now become hunting grounds for mechanical beasts. There has never been a better place to wage war.",
	$6000100: '101st Tigergruppe',
	$6000110: '7th Armoured Division, "Desert Rats"',
	$6000120: '901st Panzergrenadier Lehr Regiment',
	$6000200: 'Leningrad, Russia',
	$6000210: '0723 hrs. September 29th, 1942',
